0of%20perjury%20for%20lying%20about%20sexual%20abuse%20in%20a%20deposition%2C%20but%20dropped%20those%20charges%20after%20her%20sex-trafficking%20conviction.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fghislaine-maxwell-sex-trafficking-conviction-appeal-supreme-court-doj-epstein-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMaxwell%20is%20appealing%20her%20conviction%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBlanche%2C%20who%20was%20one%20of%20Trump's%20personal%20attorneys%20before%20being%20appointed%20second-in-command%20at%20the%20Justice%20Department%2C%20led%20the%20two-day%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20the%20prosecutors%20in%20Maxwell's%20criminal%20trial%2C%20nor%20Epstein's%20own%20sex-trafficking%20cases%2C%20which%20ended%20when%20he%20died%20in%20jail%20awaiting%20trial%2C%20were%20present.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaxwell%20was%20represented%20by%20her%20longtime%20personal%20attorney%2C%20Leah%20Saffian%2C%20and%20her%20criminal%20appeal%20lawyers%2C%20David%20Oscar%20Markus%20and%20Melissa%20Madrigal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20answers%20in%20the%20interview%20largely%20hewed%20to%20the%20main%20argument%20her%20defense%20attorneys%20presented%20in%20her%20Manhattan%20criminal%20trial%3A%20that%20Epstein%20compartmentalized%20his%20life%20and%20that%20she%20was%20not%20aware%20of%20any%20potential%20sexual%20abuse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGhislaine%20Maxwell%20is%20innocent%20and%20never%20should%20have%20been%20tried%2C%20much%20less%20convicted%2C%20in%20this%20case%2C%26quot%3B%20Markus%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BShe%20never%20committed%20or%20participated%20in%20sexual%20abuse%20against%20minors%2C%20or%20anyone%20else%2C%20for%20that%20matter.%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20interview%2C%20Maxwell%20said%20she%20had%20been%20acquainted%20with%20several%20tech%20billionaires%20%E2%80%94%20including%20Elon%20Musk%2C%20Sergey%20Brin%2C%20and%20Reid%20Hoffman%20%E2%80%94%20but%20did%20not%20accuse%20any%20of%20wrongdoing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20interview%2C%20Maxwell%20was%20moved%20from%20her%20prison%20in%20Florida%20to%20a%20lower-security%20one%20in%20Texas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Justice%20Department%20didn't%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20the%20biggest%20takeaways%20from%20the%20transcript%20of%20Maxwell's%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22eb4961fa-4108-4b5d-8515-884cbae4b5b2%5C%22%3EMaxwell%20had%20nothing%20but%20praise%20for%20Trump%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMaxwell%20told%20Blanche%20she%20first%20met%20Trump%20shortly%20after%20she%20moved%20from%20Europe%20to%20the%20United%20States%20in%201990%2C%20while%20working%20for%20her%20father%2C%20the%20British%20media%20baron%20Robert%20Maxwell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20may%20have%20met%20Donald%20Trump%20at%20that%20time%2C%20because%20my%20father%20was%20friendly%20with%20him%20and%20liked%20him%20very%20much%2C%26quot%3B%20Maxwell%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20think%20should%20be%20said%20that%20he%20also%20very%20much%20liked%20Ivana%20because%20she%20was%20also%20from%20Czechoslovakia%2C%20where%20my%20dad%20was%20from.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaxwell%20also%20praised%20the%20%26quot%3Bextraordinary%20achievement%26quot%3B%20of%20Trump's%20ascent%20to%20the%20presidency.%20When%20journalists%20asked%20in%20recent%20weeks%20whether%20he%20would%20pardon%20Maxwell%2C%20Trump%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIt%20would%20be%20inappropriate%20to%20talk%20about%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTrump%20was%20always%20very%20cordial%20and%20very%20kind%20to%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20Maxwell%20said%20in%20her%20Justice%20Department%20interview.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20just%20want%20to%20say%20that%20I%20admire%20his%20extraordinary%20achievement%20in%20becoming%20the%20President%20now.%20And%20I%20like%20him%2C%20and%20I've%20always%20liked%20him.%20So%20that%20is%20the%20sum%20and%20substance%20of%20my%20entire%20relationship%20with%20him.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAske